      passage: `Some social scientists argue that while a belief in the importance of reason and progress is key to democracy, the public&rsquo;s understanding of history is also central to its subsequent comprehension of a state&rsquo;s politics, and if an electorate is to function, historical issues cannot remain the dominion only of academics. History is too ______ to leave to historians alone.`,
      prompt: `Which choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?`,
